This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a method for compressive video measurement and reconstruction. It also utilizes optical flow in the video sequence for fast numerical algorithms. 

It is also likely to belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category as it mentions the Restricted Isometry Property (RIP) and compressed sensing theory, which are fundamental concepts in information theory. 

The paper may also belong to the optics and photonics (cs.OH) sub-category as it utilizes optical elements such as spatial light modulators (SLMs) for implementing the coded mask designs. 

The multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper deals with video data and proposes a method for compressive video measurement and reconstruction. 

Finally, the signal processing (cs.SD) sub-category is a possibility as the paper develops fast numerical algorithms which utilize temporal correlations and optical flow in the video sequence.
